The United States and the United Kingdom have announced the creation of a Joint Strategy Board. The board will analyze future challenges and how current challenges will shape future choices. It aims to integrate long-term thinking and planning into daily government work and the bilateral relationship between the two countries. The board will be co-chaired by the U.S. National Security Staff and the U.K. National Security Secretariat, and include representatives from various departments and organizations. It will meet quarterly and its mandate will be reviewed after one year.